âœª Closed Loop Congestion Control
1ï¸âƒ£  Backpressure: Nodes experiencing congestion signal back to the sender to reduce the rate of packet transmission, alleviating congestion. â®ï¸
2ï¸âƒ£  Propagation of congestion: Congestion information is propagated back through the network, affecting nodes in the opposite direction of the data flow. ğŸ”„
3ï¸âƒ£  Choke Packet Technique: Sending choke packets to inform the source of congestion and adjust its transmission rate accordingly. ğŸš¥
4ï¸âƒ£  Monitoring resource utilization: Constantly monitoring resource usage and providing feedback to nodes to reduce unnecessary traffic. ğŸ“Š
5ï¸âƒ£  Implicit Signaling: Predicting congestion based on lack of acknowledgments and adjusting transmission rates accordingly without explicit communication with congested nodes. ğŸ¤
